<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-07-09T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-07-09T00:00:00-05:00" n="526" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d526">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No 838.00/949a.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                Chargé <persName type="to">Terres</persName>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-07-09">
                                    <hi rend="italic">July 9, 1914</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>American Consul at Cape Haitien and Commander of <hi rend="italic">South
                                Carolina</hi> have been instructed to cooperate for the advancement
                            of American interests with other Americans now at Cape Haitien.
                            Commander <hi rend="italic">South Carolina</hi> further instructed to
                            proceed to Port au Prince if so desired by you to convey you from that
                            place to any part of the Republic as requested by you. Keep in constant
                            communication by wireless with <hi rend="italic">South Carolina</hi> and
                            advise Department by cable fully as to situation.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Bryan</hi></signed>.</closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>